oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Keith Bilbrey airchecks - 1988 - WSM
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Recording contains various airchecks by Keith Bilbrey (DJ), featuring phone interviews with Ricky Skaggs (performer), George Hamilton IV (performer), and a round of trivia with Kyle Cantrell, in 1988 on radio station WSM (Nashville, Tenn.)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Keith Bilbrey talks about answers for country music trivia questions -- Bilbrey talks about an upcoming Grand Ole Opry show -- Bilbrey talks about the weather and says happy birthday to Ricky Skaggs -- Ricky Skaggs talks about spending his 54th birthday in an airplane -- Bilbrey aircheck -- Bilbrey talks about the writers of the previous song -- Bilbrey reads the country almanac for the day -- Bilbrey talks about the most played jukebox tunes on this day in 1947 and Lefty Frizzell's death -- Bilbrey talks about chart topping recordings -- Bilbrey talks with George Hamilton IV about his birthday -- Bilbrey introduces Kyle Cantrell to play trivia -- Bilbrey and Cantrell invite callers to stump them with trivia questions -- Bilbrey and Cantrell answer all questions correctly -- Bilbrey aircheck
